-- Portugal CMVM market regulator suspends trade in BES
-- 
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 07:59AM EDT
-- None



LISBON, July 10 (Reuters) - Portugal's CMVM market regulator said it has suspended trading in Banco Espirito Santo <BES.LS> and is awaiting a statement by the bank, whose shares slumped earlier on Thursday.

"Trade in BES shares is suspended, we are awaiting relevant information to the market," a CMVM spokeswoman said.